Joubert, who miraculously escaped death, suffered a serious brain injury and multiple fractures.On the night of the incident, she remembered coming across Wilkens, who she said was smoking crystal meth. She grabbed the pipe from his hands and could tell by his facial expression that she had to make a run for it.According to her, she tried to run away when Wilkens grabbed her by her hair. She said he suddenly had a knife to her throat and threatened to slaughter her like a pig while repeatedly hitting her head against a wall. The police investigated Joubert s fall and a case of attempted murder was instituted.Wilkens was arrested in Noupoort, where he was undergoing rehabilitative therapy for his drug addiction.